  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Bridgette M Manning in court, in custody with attorney Amanda K. Riek.  Crystal N Long appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Waiver of Preliminary Hearing filed. Court found probable cause, bound defendant over.  Information filed, reading waived.  Rights/Elements.  Defendant pled no contest to counts 1,2, &3.  Court found guilty.  Judgment was entered.   On all counts, court withheld sentencing placed defendant on probation for 5 years.  Conditions of probation include:  Ct. 1 6 months jail, with Huber, consecutive to Milwaukee County Case 15CF504, and Juneau County Case 15CF125.  $1694.00 fines and costs.  DNA sample and surcharge of $250.00.  36 month DL revocation.  36 month IID upon licensure.  AODA and comply.  Maintain absolute sobriety.  Ct. 2 $268.00 costs.  Ct. 3 $268.00 costs.  Any traffic citations tracking with this case are dismissed.  May transfer to Dane County.  Electronic Monitoring is approved by court.  Bond on hand will be applied towards costs.
